main event: A USAFR 2nd Lieutenant reported seeing three unknown objects in the sky near Lakeland, Florida on November 7, 1955
interesting points: The objects were observed for 15 minutes.
The observer was a 2nd Lieutenant in the US Air Force Reserve.
The objects were described as probable B-47 aircraft in the area at the time.
The report mentions previous UFO sightings in the area during reconnaissance flights by capable observers.
The report states that the pilot signed the report, and the flight reports were completed through the chain of command.
